I have searched a bit, but cannot find an example in the repository where an item-type string is used while the option values are integers. As far as I can see from the state-description, an item-type string is only useful if the values are also strings.
Also the conversion from an integer to a state is quite strange and it seems it has to be done like this:
updateState(channelDoorState.getUID(), (State) new StringType(Integer.toString(NukiBindingConstants.DOORSENSOR_STATES_UNKNOWN)));
this is maybe because the project does not import the openhab libraries but:
